!!! 5
%html
  %head
    %title= 'Brendan Barr { Web Developer }'
    %link{ :href => '/css/base.css', :rel => 'stylesheet' }
  %body
    
    %header
      %h1 
        Brendan Barr
        %span{ :class => 'title' }!= "<span>{</span> Web Developer <span>}</span>"
      %nav
        %a{ :href => '#/projects', :id => 'project_link' } projects
        %a{ :href => '#/bio', :id => 'bio_link' } bio
        %a{ :href => 'http://github.com/bbarr', :class => 'external' } github
        %a{ :href => 'http://www.senselesslogic.com', :class => 'external' } blog

    #content

      %section{ :id => 'projects' }     
        %h2 Projects
        %ul                
          %li
            .inner
              %h4 
                codeci.de (beta)
                %span - Group decision making, without the fatigue.

              %p
                %a{ :href => 'http://codeci.de/', :class => 'external' } website
              
              %ol
                %li Define a problem, and then share it with whoever is in the best position to recommend an answer. People contribute and vote.
                %li Hopefully replaces those long "which library should we use for X" discussions or email threads where you end up going in circles.

          %li
            .inner
              %h4 
                Decor
                %span - Draper(rb)-inspired Javascript decorators

              %p
                %a{ :href => 'http://github.com/bbarr/decor', :class => 'external' } code

              %ol
                %li Can help create a simple ViewModel/Exhibit/Presenter/etc layer for your Javascript Application.
                %li RegExp matching for delegation targets
                %li ECMA5 setters/getters to allow transparent property delegation.

          %li
            .inner
              %h4 
                dataful.me (Not being actively developed at this point)
                %span - Self-tracking and analysis

              %p
                %a{ :href => 'http://dataful.herokuapp.com/', :class => 'external' } website
                %a{ :href => 'http://github.com/bbarr/dataful.me', :class => 'external' } code
              
              %ol
                %li Track anything as a series of tags (key or key:value)
                %li Define stats, such as "average miles (running) 1h after eating"

          %li
            .inner
              %h4 
                JSONEnforcer
                %span - JSON format validation

              %p
                %a{ :href => 'http://github.com/bbarr/jsonenforcer', :class => 'external' } code

              %ol
                %li Validates JSON structure
                %li Data-type checking
                %li Generates randomized stubs for development

          %li
            .inner
              %h4 
                MarkerJS
                %span - Javascript HTML templates

              %p
                %a{ :href => 'http://www.senselesslogic.com/2012/01/19/marker-html-templates/', :class => 'external' } website
                %a{ :href => 'http://github.com/bbarr/Marker', :class => 'external' } code
              
              %ol
                %li Chainable, HTML construction
                %li Supports reusable code via .partials()
                %li Conditionals and iterations

      %section{ :id => 'bio' }
        %h2 Bio
        %p
          I am a freelance web developer living in the Boston-Metro area, where I enjoy 
          working remotely with teams to create rich user-experiences with Ruby and Javascript.
        %p
          In my spare time, I try to remember how to play guitar and dabble a bit in game design. One day, I would like to launch a wildly successful start-up.
        %p
          Currently, I am available for work on a freelance basis.

      -#%section{ :id => 'contact' }
